<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" FontFamily="Calibri">
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Overview</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>In excercise panel user can choose excercise to run, controls it flow and set some individual excercise settings</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Structure</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>First visible element of excercise panel is combo box which contains names of all avaialable excercises. Then "Choose selection" button which enables user,
    after choice of desired excercise, to select positions on fretboard that will be included in excercise. Below, there are buttons "Start", "Pause" and "Stop" for controling
    excercise flow. At the bottom of excercise panel there is an Option panel, which hold indivdual excercise setting.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Behavior</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Excercise panel control main flow of application. Before run of any excercise, "Start" and "Choose selection" buttons are available. User should
	choose desired excercise then press "Choose selection" button which enables user to define which fret and string positions will take part in excercise.
	Then after pressing "Start" button excercise will start. During excercise run user can pause excercise (e.g. to change setting) or stop it by pressing "Stop" button.</Paragraph>
</FlowDocument>